Intro to back end unit outline
Last revised: August 14, 2015

Daily objectives: Day 1 - Day 20

Students will understand the basic components of the webâ€™s infrastructure
Students will use variables to represent values
Students will use operators to perform operations on simple values
Students will use if statements to implement basic decision making
Students will use if statements to implement complex decision making
Students will use loops to repeat blocks of code
Students will use arrays to represent groups of related data
Students will use loops to iterate over arrays and strings
Students will use associative arrays to represent groups of related data
Students will create functions to group related sections of code
Students will write to and read from files on the filesystem
Students will create, traverse, and serialize nested structures
Students will use HTML forms to gather user input
Students will use PHP to process user input from HTML forms
Students will use PHP to perform HTTP requests
Students will use HTTP requests to interact with JSON APIs
Students will implement a user authentication system
Students will implement a user authorization system
Students will use Firebase as a persistent data store
Students will initiate AJAX requests and callbacks using jQuery
